==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Macula
<hw>Mac"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Maculae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., spot, stain, blot. See
<er>Mail</er> armor, and cf. <er>Mackle</er>, <er>Macule</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A spot, as on the skin, or on the surface of the sun or
of some other luminous orb; called also
<altname>macule</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A rather large spot or blotch of
color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>macular area</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>macula lutea</ent>⟦br⟧
<mhw>
